# Clean-room construction lock. Only derived build output may be invisible
# here. The /.cursor/ and /bpk-lib/ entries died in 5.5E2g when their
# directories left the cleanroom: /bpk-lib/ was legacy working-tree residue
# (tracked source preserved on branch legacy/main) and was physically deleted
# as its own ignore comment instructed; the parallel Gate-2 implementation
# material moved to a sibling directory outside this working tree. Foreign
# material in the cleanroom must be VISIBLE contamination — an ignore entry
# that hides a parallel organism is worse than the organism.
/target/
# Python bytecode is derived build output (the interpreter's /target/): the
# Wave-2 package decomposition made the bootstrap plane importable, so the
# interpreter now materializes __pycache__ beside the packages it loads.
__pycache__/
*.pyc
# Ruff's lint cache is derived build output; gates additionally redirect it
# outside the tree (RUFF_CACHE_DIR) so it never enters a judged checkout.
.ruff_cache/
.venv/
